t the company would invest ₹ billion to accelerate its businesses in karnataka in october  general electric company acquired  billion worth of bank deposits from metlife inc in april  general electric co acquired oilfield pump maker lufkin industries for  billion in april  it was announced that ge was in talks to acquire the global power division of french engineering group alstom for a figure of around  billion a rival joint bid was submitted in june  by siemens and mitsubishi heavy industries mhi with siemens seeking to acquire alstoms gas turbine business for € billion and mhi proposing a joint venture in steam turbines plus a € billion cash investment in june  a formal offer from ge worth  billion was agreed by the alstom board part of the transaction involved the french government taking a  stake in alstom to help secure frances energy and transport interests and french jobs a rival offer from siemensmitsubishi heavy industries was rejected the acquisition was expected to be completed in  in october  ge announced it was considering the sale of its polish banking business bank bph in april  ge announced its intention to sell off its property portfolio worth  billion to wells fargo and the blackstone group it was announced in april  that general electric would sell most of its finance unit and return around  billion to shareholders as the firm looked to trim down on its holdings and rid itself of its image of a hybrid company working in both banking and manufacturing in august  ges ge capital agreed to sell its healthcare financial services business to capital one for us billion the transaction involves us billion of loans made to a wide array of sectors including senior housing hospitals medical offices outpatient services pharmaceuticals and medical devices also in august  ge capital agreed to sell ge capital banks online deposit platform to goldman sachs terms of the transaction were not disclosed but the sale includes us billion of online deposits and another us billion of brokered certificates of deposit the sale is part of ges strategic plan to exit the us banking sector and to free itself from tightening banking regulations ge also aims to shed its status as a systematically important financial institution in september  ge capital agreed to sell its transportationfinance unit to canadas bank of montreal the unit sold has us billion ca billion of assets  employees and  offices in the us and canada exact terms of the sale were not disclosed but the final price would be based on the value of the assets at closing plus a premium according to the parties in october  activist investor nelson peltzs fund trian bought a  billion stake in the company in january  haier group acquired general electrics appliance division for  billion in october  ge renewable energy agreed to pay € billion to doughty hanson  co for lm wind power during  at the end of october  it was announced that general electric was under negotiations for a deal valued at about  billion to combine ge oil and gas with baker hughes the transaction would create a publiclytraded entity controlled by ge it was announced that ge oil and gas would sell off its water treatment business as part of its divestment agreement with baker hughes the deal was cleared by the eu in may  and by the doj in june   the merger agreement was approved by shareholders at the end of june  on july   the transaction was completed and baker hughes became a ge company  in april  ge announced the name of their  million corporate headquarters would be ge innovation point the groundbreaking ceremony for the acre person campus will be held on may   and a completion date is sometime in mid stockedit ge is the only company listed in the dow jones industrial index today that was also included in the original index in  linear ge stock price graph – ge trading volume graph corporate affairsedit a general electric neon sign ge is a multinational conglomerate headquartered in boston massachusetts its main offices are located at  rockefeller plaza at rockefeller center in new york city known now as the comcast building it was formerly known as the ge building for the prominent ge logo on the roof nbcs headquarters and main studios are also located in the building through its rca subsidiary it has been associated with the center since its construction in the s ge moved its corporate headquarters from the ge building on lexington avenue to fairfield in  the company describes itself as composed of a number of primary business units or businesses each unit is itself a vast enterprise many of which would even as a standalone company rank in the fortune citation needed the list of ge businesses varies over time as the result of acquisitions divestitures and reorganizationscitation needed ges tax return is the largest return filed in the united states the  return was approximately  pages when printed out and  megabytes when submitted electronically the company also spends more on us lobbying than any other company see also fossil fuels lobby in  ge launched its ecomagination initiative in an attempt to position itself as a green company ge is one of the biggest players in the wind power industry and is developing environmentfriendly products such as hybrid locomotives desalination and water reuse solutions and photovoltaic cells the company plans to build the largest solarpanelmaking factory in the us and has set goals for its subsidiaries to lower their greenhouse gas emissions on may   ge announced it would sell its ge plastics division to petrochemicals manufacturer sabic for net proceeds of  billion the transaction took place on august   and the company name changed to sabic innovative plastics with brian gladden as ceo in february  ge announced that the company intends to close the gender gap by promising to hire and place  women in technical roles by  the company is also seeking to have a  male to female gender representation in all entrylevel technical programs ceoedit main article jeffrey r immelt this section needs additional citations for verification please help improve this article by adding citations to reliable sources unsourced material may be challenged and removed january  learn how and when to remove this template message jeffrey immelt is the chairman of the board and chief executive officer of ge he was selected by ges board of directors in  to replace jack welch following his retirement previously immelt had headed ges medical systems division now ge healthcare as its president and ceo his tenure as the chairman and ceo of ge started at a time of crisis he took over the role on september   four days before the terrorist attacks on the united states which killed two employees and cost ges insurance business  million — and had a direct effect on the companys aircraft engines sector immelt was also selected as one of president obamas financial advisors concerning the economic rescue plan on june   it was announced that immelt would step down as president and ceo immelt will retire from ge on december   john l flannery current president and chief executive of ge healthcare will take over as ceo businessesedit main article list of assets owned by general electric ges primary business divisions include ge power ge oil  gas ge renewable energy ge energy connections ge aviation ge healthcare ge transportation ge capital ge digital the former ge appliances and lighting segment was dissolved in  when ges appliance division was sold to haier for  billion ge lighting consumer lighting and the newly created current powered by ge commercial led solar ev and energy storage are now standalone businesses within the companycitation needed through these businesses ge participates in markets that include the generation transmission and distribution of electricity eg nuclear gas and solar lighting industrial automation medical imaging equipment motors railway locomotives aircraft jet engines and aviation services through ge commercial finance ge consumer finance ge equipment services and ge insurance it offers a range of financial services it has a presence in over  countries ge gauges to control a railway locomotive at a museum near saskatoon canada ge produces general imaging digital cameras since over half of ges revenue is derived from financial services it is arguably a financial company with a manufacturing arm it is also one of the largest lenders in countries other than the united states such as japan even though the first wave of conglomerates such as itt corporation lingtemcovought tenneco etc fell by the wayside by the mids in the late s another wave consisting of westinghouse tyco and others tried and failed to emulate ges success on may   it was announced that ge would auction off its appliances business for an expected sale of – billion however this plan fell through as a result of the recession as of august update ge is planning to set up a silicon carbide chip packaging rd center in coalition with suny polytechnic institute in utica new york the project will create  jobs with the potential to grow to  jobs within  years on september   ge announced the creation of a new unit ge digital which will bring together its software and it capabilities the new business unit will be headed by bill ruh who joined ge in  from cisco systems and has since worked on ges software efforts corporate recognition and rankingsedit ge sans used since  ge serif used since  in  fortune ranked ge the th largest firm in the us and the th most profitable other rankings for  include the following  company for leaders fortune  best global brand interbrand  green company newsweek  most admired company fortune  most innovative company fast company for  ges brand was valued at  billion ceo jeff immelt had a set of changes in the presentation of the brand commissioned in  after he took the reins as chairman to unify the diversified businesses of gecitation needed the changes included a new corporate color palette small modifications to the ge logo a new customized font ge inspira and a new slogan imagination at work composed by david lucas to replace the slogan we bring good things to life used since  the standard requires many headlines to be lowercased and adds visual white space to documents and advertising the changes were designed by wolff olins and are used on ges marketing literature and website in  a second typeface family was introduced ge sans and serif by bold monday created under art direction by wolff olins fortune edit year rank                                           as of  ge had appeared on the fortune  list for  years and held the th rank controversies and criticismedit the six reactors in the  fukushima ii nuclear power plant catastrophe had been designed by general electric their design had been criticised as far back as  in march  the new york times reported that despite earning  billion in worldwide profits including more than  billion from us operations general electric did not owe taxes in  general electric had a tax refund of  billion this same article also pointed out that ge has reduced its american workforce by one fifth since  the times also reported that general electric had been engineering tax reductions starting with the fees paid on its  new york state charter in december  the nonpartisan organization public campaign criticized general electric for spending  million on lobbying and not paying any taxes during – instead getting  billion in tax rebates despite making a profit of  billion laying off  workers since  and increasing executive pay by  to  million in  for the top  executives between march  and february  general electric was fined or ordered to pay damages by a court  times amounting to at least  according to a report from the multinational monitor general electric was one of the pioneers and early widespread adopters of planned obsolescence with a major part in the phoebus cartel there has been protest regarding state grants and tax relief promised to ge prior to their decision to move their headquarters to boston environmental recordedit pollutionedit ge has a history of some of its activities giving rise to largescale air and water pollution based on year  data researchers at the political economy research institute listed the corporation as the fourthlargest corporate producer of air pollution in the united states with more than  million pounds per year  tons of toxic chemicals released into the air ge has also been implicated in the creation of toxic waste according to epa documents only the united states government honeywell and chevron corporation are responsible for producing more superfund toxic waste sites in  new york state attorney general robert abrams filed suit in the united states district court for the northern district of new york to compel ge to pay for the cleanup of what was claimed to be more than  tons of chemicals dumped from their plant in waterford new york in  the company agreed to pay a  million settlement in connection with claims it polluted the housatonic river pittsfield massachusetts and other sites with polychlorinated biphenyls pcbs and other hazardous substances in  acting on concerns that the plan proposed by ge did not provide for adequate protection of public health and the environment the united states environmental protection agency issued a unilateral administrative order for the company to address cleanup at the ge site in rome georgia also contaminated with pcbs the nuclear reactors involved in the  crisis at fukushima i in japan are ge designs and the architectural designs were done by ebasco formerly owned by ge concerns over the design and safety of these reactors were raised as early as  but tsunami danger was not discussed at that time as of update the same model nuclear power reactors designed by ge are operating in the us such as the controversial pilgrim nuclear generating station in plymouth massachusetts pollution of the hudson riveredit main article pollution of the hudson river general electric heavily contaminated the hudson river with polychlorinated biphenyls pcbs between  and  this pollution caused a range of harmful effects to wildlife and people who eat fish from the river or drink the water in response to the contamination activists protested in various ways musician pete seeger founded the hudson river sloop clearwater and the clearwater festival to draw attention to the problem in  the united states environmental protection agency epa declared a mile  km stretch of the river from hudson falls to new york city to be a superfund site requiring cleanup this superfund site is considered to be one of the largest in the nation other sources of pollution including mercury contamination and sewage dumping have also contributed to problems in the hudson river watershed pollution of the housatonic riveredit from c  until  general electric polluted the housatonic river with pcb discharges from its plant at pittsfield massachusetts epa designated the pittsfield plant and several miles of the housatonic to be a superfund site in  and ordered ge to remediate the site aroclor  and aroclor  made by monsanto was the primary contaminant of the pollution the highest concentrations of pcbs in the housatonic river are found in woods pond in lenox massachusetts just south of pittsfield where they have been measured up to  mgkg in the sediment about  of all the pcbs currently in the river are estimated to be retained in the sediment behind woods pond dam this is estimated to be about  pounds of pcbs former filled oxbows are also polluted waterfowl and fish who live in and around the river contain significant levels of pcbs and can present health risks if consumed environmental initiativesedit on june   ge announced that it has licensed solar thermal technology from californiabased esolar for use in power plants that use both solar and natural gas on may   ge unveiled its ev solar carport a carport that incorporates solar panels on its roof with electric vehicle charging stations under its cover in may  ge announced the launch of a program called ecomagination intended in the words of ceo jeff immelt to develop tomorrows solutions such as solar energy hybrid locomotives fuel cells loweremission aircraft engines lighter and stronger durable materials efficient lighting and water purification technology the announcement prompted an oped piece in the new york times to observe that while general electrics increased emphasis on clean technology will probably result in improved products and benefit its bottom line mr immelts credibility as a spokesman on national environmental policy is fatally flawed because of his companys intransigence in cleaning up its own toxic legacy ge facility in schenectady new york ge has said that it will invest  billion in clean technology research and development in  as part of its ecomagination initiative as of october  the scheme had resulted in  green products being brought to market ranging from halogen lamps to biogas engines in  ge raised the annual revenue target for its ecomagination initiative from  billion in  to  billion following positive market response to its new product lines in  ge continued to raise its investment by adding  billion into ecomagination over the next five years ge general electric energys renewable energy business has expanded greatly to keep up with growing us and global demand for clean energy since entering the renewable energy industry in  ge has invested more than  million in renewable energy commercialization in august  it acquired kelman ltd a northern ireland company specializing in advanced monitoring and diagnostics technologies for transformers used in renewable energy generation and announced an expansion of its business in northern ireland in may  in  ges renewable energy initiatives which include solar power wind power and ge jenbacher gas engines using renewable and nonrenewable methanebased gases employ more than  people globally and have created more than  supporting jobs ge energy and orion new zealand limited orion have announced implementation of the first phase of a ge network management system to help improve power reliability for customers ges enmac distribution management system is the foundation of orions initiative the system of smart grid technologies will significantly improve the network companys ability to manage big network emergencies and help it to restore power faster when outages occur educational initiativesedit ge healthcare is collaborating with the wayne state university school of medicine and the medical university of south carolina to offer an integrated radiology curriculum during their respective md programs led by investigators of the advanced diagnostic ultrasound in microgravity study ge has donated over one million dollars of logiq e ultrasound equipment to these two institutions marketing initiativesedit – contentmarketing campaignsedit between september  and april  ge ran a content marketing campaign dedicated to telling the stories of innovators—people who are reshaping the world through act or invention the initiative included  minute films from leading documentary film directors albert maysles jessica yu leslie iwerks steve james alex gibney lixin fan gary hustwit and others and a usergenerated competition that received over  submissions out of which  finalist were chosen short films big ideas was launched at the  toronto international film festival in partnership with cinelan stories included breakthroughs in slingshot water vapor distillation system cancer research energy production pain management and food access each of the  films received world premiere screenings at a major international film festival including the sundance film festival and the tribeca film festival the winning amateur director film the cyborg foundation was awarded a us prize at the  at sundance film festivalcitation needed according to ge the campaign garnered more than  billion total media impressions  million online views and was seen in  countriescitation needed sponsorshipsedit see also general electric theater in january  general electric signed an estimated  million deal with the boston celtics to have its corporate logo put on the nba teams jersey legal issuesedit on august   the sec fined ge  million for violating accounting rules in two separate cases misleading investors into believing ge would meet or beat earnings expectations ge has faced criminal action regarding its defense related operations ge was convicted in  of defrauding the us department of defense and again in  on charges of corrupt practices in the sale of jet engines to israel a geowned abandoned building resides on seaview avenue in bridgeport connecticut the abandoned property has been cited in crimes that include being used as a hideout for a yearold thief in  defence lawyers included craig bridges and tony weimar  political affiliationedit in the s ge sponsored ronald reagans tv career and launched him on the lecture circuit as a crusader against big government although it can be argued that ge frequently supported conservative policies ges record with designing social programs supporting civil rights organizations and funding minority education programs speaks to their effort to support philanthropic programs and progressive causes notable appearances in mediaedit ge was the primary focus of a  short subject academy awardwinning documentary deadly deception general electric nuclear weapons and our environment that juxtaposed ges we bring good things to life commercials with the true stories of workers and neighbors whose lives have been affected by the companys activities involving nuclear weapons in the early s kurt vonnegut was a writer for general electric a number of his novels and stories notably cats cradle refer to the fictional city of ilium which appears to be loosely based on schenectady new york  the ilium works is the setting for the short story deer in the works in  ge received a national jefferson award for outstanding service by a major corporation in  ge won a clio award for its  soft white light bulbs commercial we bring good things to life the slogan we bring good things to life was created by phil dusenberry at the ad agency bbdo see alsoedit companies portal edison engineering development program ge global research ge technology infrastructure knolls atomic power laboratory list of assets owned by general electric phoebus cartel top  us federal contractors ge hitachi nuclear energy referencesedit notes  certificate of incorporation ge ge retrieved january     a b fact sheet about us ge retrieved august     vaccaro adam august   general electric moves into temporary headquarters in boston bostoncom retrieved september   today ges global headquarters officially moved to boston were happy to be here official tweet from ge on august     httpwwwcnbccomgeneralelectricsimmeltissteppingdownjohnflannerynamedchairmanandceohtml  a b c d e f financial statements for general electric company google finance retrieved february     company search edgar system securities and exchange commission header retrieved december     summary of operating segments pdf ge retrieved january     resolute innovation resoluteinnovationcom retrieved    a b fortune   fortune  retrieved june     a b fortune  most profitable companies ibm fortune  retrieved december     general electric forbes retrieved june    heritage of research general electric retrieved june     boston lands new ge headquarters boston globe retrieved january     mann ted kamp jon january   general electric to move headquarters to boston the wall street journal retrieved january     ge moves headquarters to boston press release general electric january   retrieved september     arnold horace l modern machineshop economics part ii in engineering magazine    electricity a brief history of con edison con edison archived from the original 